    },
    {
      "id": "570619d5e79f30763b739d26fe3ef58465e65d75",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2016-05-23 17:13:31.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4: Code-Review-1\n\nAndreas: Do we really need one more patch to ldiskfs on both rhel7 AND rhel6?\n\nrhel6 still returns NULL and so I thin kto minimize number of patches, checking bh for NULL and retaining htat part of old loginc in osd code should be fine while picking up error from ERR_PTR if any was provided.\n\n-1 because it breaks rhel6 now.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "228205b326c523b466008e8f7317d4de29eca0a7",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 301,
        "name": "Dmitry Eremin",
        "email": "dmitry.eremin@intel.com",
        "username": "dmiter",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2016-05-23 23:41:16.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nWhich test on rhel6 is it break?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "6eae2ab85c42144ed61f6c95e2d69f891b724a91",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
      },
      "date": "2016-05-24 01:09:52.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nIt does not break a test, it breaks error handling on rhel6 because rhel6 ldiskfs always returns NULL on error from that find entry function and you always expect ERR_PTR().\n\nIf we do want to patch ldiskfs - then we'd need to include at least rhel6 version of it into this patch or linked to it closely so that the two could be landed together and not introduce this regression into master (rhel7 is already broken of course, just broken in a different way in your patch than without so that ldiskfs patch is a bit less important).",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "9b223b5921e791070204c53cdf35d7bb12615546",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 301,
        "name": "Dmitry Eremin",
        "email": "dmitry.eremin@intel.com",
        "username": "dmiter",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2016-05-24 02:52:54.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\nThe NULL is replaced with ERR_PTR(-ENOENT) in osd_internal.h. So, there is no NULL will be passed as return value. This define emulate later behavior in rhel7.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
    {
      "id": "7a23a50c285fb2f698821a5120c8103ca7f72565",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 112,
        "name": "Oleg Drokin",
        "email": "green@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "green"
